The paper deals with the state complexity of regular languages and their binary operations, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also involves the study of regular and ideal languages, which are related to automata theory and computational complexity (cs.DS). The paper presents tight upper bounds for the state complexity of binary operations, which involves combinatorial and algorithmic techniques (cs.CC). The study of state complexity also has connections to logic and algebra, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.LO and cs.IT.
